g.daum.net|date=|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n*15th Chemical Battalion (''\uc81c15\ud654\uc0dd\ubc29\ub300\ub300 \u2013 je 15 Hwasangbang Daedae'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mil/article/227283/greywolf_brigade_conducts_complex_combined_breach_training_with_rok_army_partners|title=Greywolf Brigade conducts complex combined breach training with ROK Army partners|website=army.mil|date=18 September 2019|author=Scott Kuhn|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n*17th Chemical Battalion (''\uc81c17\ud654\uc0dd\ubc29\ub300\ub300 \u2013 je 17 Hwasangbang Daedae'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://brunch.co.kr/@militarybox/60 |title=7th Corps|website=brunch.co.kr|date=6 February 2018|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n*19th Chemical Battalion (''\uc81c19\ud654\uc0dd\ubc29\ub300\ub300 \u2013 je 19 Hwasangbang Daedae'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mil/article/178506/team_19_conducts_combined_decontamination_exercise_with_rok_army|title=Team 19 Conducts Combined Decontamination Exercise with ROK Army|website=army.mil|author=Sung Guk un|date=18 November 2016|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Sri Lanka==\n*Nuclear Biological Chemical Defense School<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nma.navy.lk/index.php?id=124|title=NBCD SCHOOL|website=nma.navy.lk|date=|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n", "text_old": "Several countries around the world maintain military units that are specifically trained to cope with CBRN (Chemical, Biological, Radiological, Nuclear) threats. Beside this specialized units, most modern armed forces undergo generalized basic CBRN self-defense training for all their personnel. \n\n{{TOC right}}\n==Albania==\n* Central Laboratory of the Armed Forces \u2013 Military Unit Nr.4010 ('' Laboratori Qendror i Forcave t\u00eb Armatosura - Rep. Usht. Nr.4010'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aaf.mil.al/index.php/brigada-logjistike/159-struktura/4356-laboratori-qendror-i-forcave-te-armatosura-rep-usht-nr-4010|title=Laboratori Qendror i F